  "prompt": "How can I install WordPress in a folder?",
  "response": "Here's a step-by-step guide to installing WordPress in a specific folder:\n\n1. Download WordPress\n- Go to wordpress.org and download the latest version\n- Extract the WordPress files\n\n2. Upload to Specific Folder\n- Use FTP (FileZilla) or File Manager in cPanel\n- Create a new folder in your website's public_html directory\n- Upload all WordPress files to this folder\n\n3. Create a MySQL Database\n- In cPanel, go to MySQL Databases\n- Create a new database\n- Create a database user\n- Assign user privileges to the database\n\n4. Configure WordPress\n- Navigate to your folder's URL (e.g., yourdomain.com/wordpress)\n- Run the WordPress installation\n- Enter database details from step 3\n- Complete the setup wizard\n\n5. Alternative Method: Subdomains\n- Create a subdomain in cPanel\n- Point it to the folder containing WordPress\n- Install WordPress in that subdomain directory\n\n6. Using Softaculous (If Available)\n- In cPanel, find Softaculous Apps Installer\n- Select WordPress\n- Choose installation directory\n- Complete installation\n\nTips:\n- Ensure proper file permissions\n- Use .htaccess for URL redirects if needed\n- Keep WordPress and plugins updated",
